   ELECTR NETWORK, MAR 29-31, 2020},
Organization = {Inst Elect \& Elect Engineers; IEEE Comp Soc},
Abstract = {Due to the increasing availability and functionality of image editing
   tools, many forensic techniques such as digital image authentication,
   source identification and tamper detection are important for forensic
   image analysis. In this paper, we describe a machine learning based
   system to address the forensic analysis of scanner devices. The proposed
   system uses deep-learning to automatically learn the intrinsic features
   from various scanned images. Our experimental results show that high
   accuracy can he achieved for source scanner identification. The proposed
   system can also generate a reliability map that indicates the
   manipulated regions in an scanned image.},
