Note = {2nd IEEE World Conference on Communication and Computing (WCONF),
   Kalinga Univ, Raipur, INDIA, JUL 12-14, 2024},
Organization = {IEEE; Govt India, Dept Sci \& Technol, Sci \& Engn Res Board; IEEE Tech
   Comm; IEEE MP Sect},
Abstract = {Morse code is a method used in telecommunication to encode text
   characters as sequences of two different signal durations, called dots
   and dashes, or dits and dahs. It is a well-known, traditional method of
   communication that is frequently connected to radio transmission and
   telegraphy. In today's world, to protect sensitive data from
   cyber-attacks and maintain privacy and integrity in digital
   conversations, transactions, and storage, encryption and decryption are
   essential. These procedures provide security and build user confidence
   in this age of cybercrime by ensuring that their data is protected from
   unauthorized access. Advanced Encryption Standard (AES) is a popular
   encryption model which to date has been trusted for its effectiveness in
   safeguarding sensitive data in digital communications and storage. AES
   Modern innovations also include other new mechanisms like - artificial
   intelligence (AI) to support pattern recognition, which later reduces
   the need for human decryption efforts for decryption and also improves
   the speed and efficiency of decryption of encrypted data. Various
   techniques such as artificial intelligence or machine learning are also
   used in decryption techniques. In the current interconnected digital
   environment, this integration contributes not only to enhancing the
   efficiency of encrypting but also allows for faster decryption of data
   for accurate and timely transmission of data. To make this research more
   realistic, data is transmitted between two systems using a wireless LAN
   connection. Besides this, the evaluation of these models is done based
   on the time taken for the encryption process and decryption process to
   ensure the efficiency is optimally vested in real life.},
