Abstract = {The criminal activities in the bitcoin market have been represented by
   hacks since the beginnings of cryptocurrency transactions. Ransomware
   attacks are one of the most dangerous related crimes in the coins
   market; this type of malware forces victims to pay after encryption of
   the victim's file. This paper aims at analysing this context using
   machine learning techniques through bitcoin transactions data set. The
   baseline data set containing all the attributes has been compared with
   two reduced subsets applying feature selection methods in an independent
   way: ExtendedCorrelation-based Feature Selection (eCFS)
   andCorrelation-based Feature Selection with Exhaustive Search (XCFS).
   C4.5 algorithm from the trees' family, PART, which is a rule-based
   classifier, and kNN, which is lazy algorithm, have been selected to
   achieve our results. We focus on the kappa and accuracy performance
   metrics to evaluate on unseen data the trained classification models.},
