Volume = {11},
Number = {3},
Pages = {112-125},
Month = {SEP},
Abstract = {With the rapid development of big data technology, the investigative
   interrogation mode is also facing new challenges and opportunities. This
   paper discusses the impact and changes of big data technology on the
   investigative interrogation mode through the research on the
   investigative interrogation mode under the background of big data. First
   of all, big data technology provides more data sources and analysis
   methods for investigation and interrogation. The traditional
   investigation and interrogation mode mainly relies on manual collection
   and analysis of information, while big data technology can obtain data
   from various channels, and through data mining and analysis, extract
   useful information and clues, and provide more comprehensive and
   accurate information for investigation and interrogation. support.
   Secondly, big data technology can also strengthen the predictive ability
   of investigation and interrogation. Through the analysis and mining of
   big data, some laws and trends hidden behind the data can be discovered,
   so as to predict possible future events and criminal behaviors, and
   provide more scientific and accurate guidance for investigation and
   interrogation. However, big data technology also brings some challenges
   and problems. First of all, the processing and analysis of big data
   consumes a lot of computing resources and time, and requires the
   investigative department to have corresponding technical and equipment
   support. Secondly, the use of big data also needs to pay attention to
   issues such as privacy protection and data security, so as to avoid
   violating the rights and interests of citizens and causing unnecessary
   losses. The impact of big data technology on the investigative
   interrogation model is multi-faceted, which not only brings new
   opportunities and challenges, but also requires the investigative
   department to pay attention to technical and ethical issues when using
   it. In the future, with the continuous development and application of
   big data technology, the investigation and interrogation model will also
   be continuously updated and improved to provide stronger support for
   fighting crime.},
