Title = {RETRACTED: Digital Proof Collective Model Using Integrated Fusion Data
   Modelling (Retracted Article)},
Journal = {WIRELESS PERSONAL COMMUNICATIONS},
Year = {2022},
Volume = {127},
Number = {SUPPL 1, 1},
Pages = {11},
Month = {DEC},
Abstract = {Data security is critical, and security measures vary depending on the
   services and applications. The collection, analysis, and auditing of
   digital evidence, especially in forensic investigations, necessitates a
   high level of security and data analytics. The ultimate purpose is to
   preserve multimedia data in an inspection paradigm relying on auto
   classify and effective deduplication techniques. Information is more
   useful in legal, human rights, and crime investigation comparisons than
   in other data consumption applications. In the present situation, where
   there are a large number of witnesses at crime scenes, digital data or
   virtual proofs play an important role in the justice system. Virtual
   evidence security is in high demand in the forensic and criminal justice
   sectors. When the public wants to share virtual proof and facts, a
   reliable and efficient channel between the user and the server is
   needed. A digital forensic administrator must oversee the evidence
   transaction in the digital realm. Traditional third-party administrator
   auditing is needed when using the virtual proof collection system. When
   the proof is gathered, our proposed modal, which is incorporated, then
   based on data analytics, if many users exchanged, then the data becomes
   familiar unless unfamiliar. Check familiarity status has been set as the
   threshold value. This template fusion modal aids in the investigation
   and virtual proofing of data protection, as well as data analytics for
   successful deduplication.},
