Number = {4},
Pages = {342-348},
Abstract = {Data science emerged as a popular technical field by leveraging the
   advances in data storage, computing, and machine learning. Practical
   applications of data science are far-reaching and include marketing,
   fraud detection, logistics, crime prediction, social engagement, sports
   team management, and health care. Recognizing this profound impact, the
   Johns Hopkins University Applied Physics Laboratory (APL) Asymmetric
   Operations Sector (AOS) created the Data Science Initiative (DSI) to
   apply data science to national security challenges and health care. The
   DSI accelerated APL data science contributions to national security and
   health care by creating new research initiatives and establishing deep
   technical competencies that shaped and directed novel solutions across
   the AOS mission space.},
